{{Orphan|date=June 2014}} The '''Cool Capital Biennale''' is a citywide art, architecture and design biennale convened by [[Pieter J Mathews|Pieter Mathews]].<ref name="DEKAT cc">{{cite journal|journal=DEKAT|date=December 2012|page=16}}{{full citation needed|date=June 2014}}</ref><ref name="SAIA web">{{cite web|title=Pieter Mathews|url=http://saia.org.za/?p=1039|publisher=[[South African Institute of Architects]]|accessdate=2 April 2014}}</ref><ref name="Innovate AHMP">{{cite journal|last=Steenberg|first=Renate|title=Alumnus showcases talent for innovative design|journal=Innovate:|date=2013|issue=8|pages=36–38|url=http://web.up.ac.za/sitefiles/file/44/1026/2163/8121/Innovate%208/36-39%20Alumnus_showcase_talent_for_innovative_design%20by%20Renate%20Steenberg.pdf|accessdate=25 March 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505015902/http://web.up.ac.za/sitefiles/file/44/1026/2163/8121/Innovate%208/36-39%20Alumnus_showcase_talent_for_innovative_design%20by%20Renate%20Steenberg.pdf|archivedate=5 May 2014|df=}}</ref> This bi-annual event is held in the [[Pretoria|City of Pretoria]] and allows for anyone to contribute something creative,<ref name="IOL Pta News">{{cite web|last=de Beer|first=Diane|title=Upping Pretoria’s cool cred|url=http://www.iol.co.za/tonight/what-s-on/gauteng/upping-pretoria-s-cool-cred-1.1655894#.UxnBxmfNvct|work=IOL|date=4 March 2014|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> being an "uncurated, DIY, guerrilla biennale".<ref name="IOL Pta News" /> It aims to bring change to Pretoria and expose residents to art, architecture and design.<ref name="DEKAT cc2">{{cite journal|journal=DEKAT|date=March–April 2014|page=90}}{{full citation needed|date=June 2014}}</ref> It is web based, with a catalogue being published at the end of each event year.<ref name="Foreign Guide">{{cite journal|title=Cool Capital Biennale 2014|journal=The South African FOREIGN Guide|year=2013/2014|volume=15|url=http://www.foreignguide.com}}</ref> Interventions<ref name="Beeld artkl">{{cite news|last=Myburg|first=Johan|title=Doen-kuns-self in 'cool Pta'|newspaper=Beeld|date=21 February 2014}}</ref> include:
* Showing of Pretoria-focused films. * Bus tours (e.g. to [[Marabastad, Pretoria|Marabastad]]). * Visiting buildings that are usually not open to the public. * "Gallery Crawling". * An urban party in the CBD. * Poetry in malls. * The [http://www.dutchfootsteps.co.za Dutch Footsteps] website. * Sculpture exhibitions.
