[[File:MIFGS 2008 Reflections.jpg|thumb|2008 Gold Show Garden Award winner "Reflections", designed by Christian Jenkins Design]]
The '''Melbourne International Flower and Garden Show''' is a [[flower show]] held annually since 1995 in early April each year, in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]]. It is located in the [[World Heritage Site]] of [[Carlton Gardens, Melbourne|Carlton Gardens]] and the [[Royal Exhibition Building]].<ref name="Hopkins">[https://books.google.com/books?id=QTrs8X7cj90C&pg=PA271&dq=%22Melbourne+International+Flower+and+Garden+Show%22+history&hl=en&sa=X&ei=w-b7Tuf5As6UmQXEy5jfDQ&ved=0CEIQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=%22Melbourne%20International%20Flower%20and%20Garden%20Show%22%20history&f=false Graeme Hopkins and Christine Goodwin: ''Living Architecture: Green Roofs and Walls''], 2011, pg.271</ref> It is the largest [[horticulture|horticultural]] event in the southern hemisphere, attracting over 100,000 visitors.<ref name="Hopkins"/> It is rated among the top five flower and garden shows in the world.

